{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_a20dc6ba529049eab28813ee","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t[build-system]\n2\trequires = [\"setuptools>=61\", \"wheel\"]\n3\tbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n4\t\n5\t[project]\n6\tname = \"flavio\"\n7\tversion = \"2.7.0\"\n8\tauthors = [\n9\t    {name = \"David M. Straub\", email = \"straub@protonmail.com\"},\n10\t]\n11\tdescription = \"A Python package for flavour physics phenomenology in the Standard Model and beyond\"\n12\treadme = {file = \"README.md\", content-type = \"text/markdown\"}\n13\tlicense = {text = \"MIT\"}\n14\trequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n15\tdependencies = [\n16\t    \"numpy>=1.20.0\",\n17\t    \"scipy\",\n18\t    \"pyyaml\",\n19\t    \"ckmutil>=1.2.0\",\n20\t    \"wilson>=2.5\",\n21\t    \"particle>=0.21.0\",\n22\t    \"parton>=0.2.1\",\n23\t]\n24\t\n25\t[project.optional-dependencies]\n26\ttesting = [\"pytest\"]\n27\tplotting = [\"matplotlib>=2.0\"]\n28\tsampling = [\"iminuit>=2.0\"]\n29\t\n30\t[project.urls]\n31\tHomepage = \"https://flav-io.github.io\"\n32\t\n33\t[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n34\tinclude = [\"flavio*\"]\n35\t\n36\t[tool.setuptools.package-data]\n37\tflavio = [\n38\t    \"data/*.yml\",\n39\t    \"data/test/*\",\n40\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-0810-4077v3/*\",\n41\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-1503-05534v1/*\",\n42\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-1503-05534v2/*\",\n43\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-1501-00367v2/*\",\n44\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-1602-01399v1/*\",\n45\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-1811-00983v1/*\",\n46\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-2102.07233v2/*\",\n47\t    \"physics/data/arXiv-2305-06301v1/*\",\n48\t    \"physics/data/qcdf_interpolate/*\",\n49\t    \"physics/data/wcsm/*\",\n50\t]\n51\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b067217c-9ebf-429f-96ed-59bb69067459","uuid":"78947d5d-0c71-4d67-9cdd-671f5e373bcf","timestamp":"2026-04-08T23:44:26.593Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/pyproject.toml","content":"[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"flavio\"\nversion = \"2.7.0\"\nauthors = [\n    {name = \"David M. Straub\", email = \"straub@protonmail.com\"},\n]\ndescription = \"A Python package for flavour physics phenomenology in the Standard Model and beyond\"\nreadme = {file = \"README.md\", content-type = \"text/markdown\"}\nlicense = {text = \"MIT\"}\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = [\n    \"numpy>=1.20.0\",\n    \"scipy\",\n    \"pyyaml\",\n    \"ckmutil>=1.2.0\",\n    \"wilson>=2.5\",\n    \"particle>=0.21.0\",\n    \"parton>=0.2.1\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\ntesting = [\"pytest\"]\nplotting = [\"matplotlib>=2.0\"]\nsampling = [\"iminuit>=2.0\"]\n\n[project.urls]\nHomepage = \"https://flav-io.github.io\"\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\ninclude = [\"flavio*\"]\n\n[tool.setuptools.package-data]\nflavio = [\n    \"data/*.yml\",\n    \"data/test/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-0810-4077v3/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-1503-05534v1/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-1503-05534v2/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-1501-00367v2/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-1602-01399v1/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-1811-00983v1/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-2102.07233v2/*\",\n    \"physics/data/arXiv-2305-06301v1/*\",\n    \"physics/data/qcdf_interpolate/*\",\n    \"physics/data/wcsm/*\",\n]\n","numLines":51,"startLine":1,"totalLines":51}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_8edc768019f44d38b3a850a0","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/flav-io/flavio\">![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/flav-io/flavio.svg?branch=master)</a> [![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/repos/github/flav-io/flavio/badge.svg)](https://coveralls.io/github/flav-io/flavio) [![DOI](https://zenodo.org/badge/22356/flav-io/flavio.svg)](https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/22356/flav-io/flavio)\n2\t\n3\t# flavio – flavour phenomenology in the Standard model and beyond\n4\t\n5\tflavio is a Python package to compute observables in flavour physics, electroweak precision tests, Higgs physics,\n6\tand other precision tests of the Standard Model, both in\n7\tthe Standard Model and in the presence of new physics encoded in Wilson\n8\tcoefficients of dimension-6 operators.\n9\t\n10\t## Project web site\n11\t\n12\tFurther information and the package documentation can be found at:\n13\t\n14\thttp://flav-io.github.io\n15\t\n16\tThis web site is built with Jekyll and hosted on Github pages. You can check\n17\tout its source (or submit pull requests) at https://github.com/flav-io/flav-io.github.io.\n18\t\n19\t## Installation\n20\t\n21\tSee http://flav-io.github.io/docs/installation.html for instructions.\n22\t\n23\t## Bugs and feature request\n24\t\n25\tPlease submit questions, bugs and feature request using\n26\t[Github's issue system](https://github.com/flav-io/flavio/issues) rather than\n27\tby E-mail. Thanks!\n28\t\n29\t\n30\t\n31\t## Contributors\n32\t\n33\tMaintainer:\n34\t\n35\t- Peter Stangl (@peterstangl)\n36\t\n37\tOriginal author:\n38\t\n39\t- David M. Straub (@DavidMStraub)\n40\t\n41\tContributors (in alphabetical order):\n42\t\n43\t- Jason Aebischer\n44\t- Jorge Alda Gallo\n45\t- Frederik Beaujean\n46\t- Anja Beck\n47\t- Alexandre Carvunis\n48\t- Adam Falkowski\n49\t- Tobias Felkl\n50\t- Ece Gürler\n51\t- Matěj Hudec\n52\t- Matthew Kirk\n53\t- Dmytro Kovalskyi\n54\t- Jonathan Kriewald\n55\t- Girish Kumar\n56\t- Jacky Kumar\n57\t- Christoph Langenbruch\n58\t- Christoph Niehoff\n59\t- Markus Prim\n60\t- Albert Puig\n61\t- Méril Reboud\n62\t- Stefanie Reichert\n63\t- Niladri Sahoo\n64\t- Jakub Šalko\n65\t- Michael Schmidt\n66\t- Aleks Smolkovič\n67\t- Peter Stangl\n68\t- Olcyr Sumensari\n69\t- Felicia Volle\n70\t- Zeren Simon Wang\n71\t\n72\t## License\n73\t\n74\tflavio is released under the MIT license.\n75\t\n76\t## Citation\n77\t\n78\tIf you use flavio in a scientific publication, please cite:\n79\t\n80\t> D. Straub, \"flavio: a Python package for flavour and precision\n81\tphenomenology in the Standard Model and beyond\", [arXiv:1810.08132](https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.08132)\n82\t\n83\tThis paper contains many references to results in the literature that went\n84\tinto the code. Please also consider citing the relevant original literature,\n85\twhere the real work was done.\n86\t\n87\tThe flavio repository itself is also citable via a DOI provided by Zenodo:\n88\t\n89\t[![DOI](https://zenodo.org/badge/22356/flav-io/flavio.svg)](https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/22356/flav-io/flavio)\n90\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b067217c-9ebf-429f-96ed-59bb69067459","uuid":"d879395a-68e4-436c-87fb-ac726c7f3bc4","timestamp":"2026-04-08T23:44:26.595Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"<a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/flav-io/flavio\">![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/flav-io/flavio.svg?branch=master)</a> [![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/repos/github/flav-io/flavio/badge.svg)](https://coveralls.io/github/flav-io/flavio) [![DOI](https://zenodo.org/badge/22356/flav-io/flavio.svg)](https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/22356/flav-io/flavio)\n\n# flavio – flavour phenomenology in the Standard model and beyond\n\nflavio is a Python package to compute observables in flavour physics, electroweak precision tests, Higgs physics,\nand other precision tests of the Standard Model, both in\nthe Standard Model and in the presence of new physics encoded in Wilson\ncoefficients of dimension-6 operators.\n\n## Project web site\n\nFurther information and the package documentation can be found at:\n\nhttp://flav-io.github.io\n\nThis web site is built with Jekyll and hosted on Github pages. You can check\nout its source (or submit pull requests) at https://github.com/flav-io/flav-io.github.io.\n\n## Installation\n\nSee http://flav-io.github.io/docs/installation.html for instructions.\n\n## Bugs and feature request\n\nPlease submit questions, bugs and feature request using\n[Github's issue system](https://github.com/flav-io/flavio/issues) rather than\nby E-mail. Thanks!\n\n\n\n## Contributors\n\nMaintainer:\n\n- Peter Stangl (@peterstangl)\n\nOriginal author:\n\n- David M. Straub (@DavidMStraub)\n\nContributors (in alphabetical order):\n\n- Jason Aebischer\n- Jorge Alda Gallo\n- Frederik Beaujean\n- Anja Beck\n- Alexandre Carvunis\n- Adam Falkowski\n- Tobias Felkl\n- Ece Gürler\n- Matěj Hudec\n- Matthew Kirk\n- Dmytro Kovalskyi\n- Jonathan Kriewald\n- Girish Kumar\n- Jacky Kumar\n- Christoph Langenbruch\n- Christoph Niehoff\n- Markus Prim\n- Albert Puig\n- Méril Reboud\n- Stefanie Reichert\n- Niladri Sahoo\n- Jakub Šalko\n- Michael Schmidt\n- Aleks Smolkovič\n- Peter Stangl\n- Olcyr Sumensari\n- Felicia Volle\n- Zeren Simon Wang\n\n## License\n\nflavio is released under the MIT license.\n\n## Citation\n\nIf you use flavio in a scientific publication, please cite:\n\n> D. Straub, \"flavio: a Python package for flavour and precision\nphenomenology in the Standard Model and beyond\", [arXiv:1810.08132](https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.08132)\n\nThis paper contains many references to results in the literature that went\ninto the code. Please also consider citing the relevant original literature,\nwhere the real work was done.\n\nThe flavio repository itself is also citable via a DOI provided by Zenodo:\n\n[![DOI](https://zenodo.org/badge/22356/flav-io/flavio.svg)](https://zenodo.org/badge/latestdoi/22356/flav-io/flavio)\n","numLines":90,"startLine":1,"totalLines":90}}}
